<p><strong>Add On: </strong>Just north of Lake Garda, the Dolomites is home to some unique towns that have a quirky mix of Italian and Austrian influences. It’s a great foodie region with the biggest concentration of Michelin-starred restaurants in Italy and fantastic wineries that produce some great labels. It’s also home to stunning walking and cycling trails so all that irresistible food can be enjoyed guilt-free.</p>
